Jenkins Pipeline (Groovy Format)

         1. Scripted Pipeline- A Jenkins pipeline defined in Groovy code with full programmatic control and flexibility.

Comp use 2. Declarative Pipeline- A Jenkins pipeline defined in a structured, predefined syntax that is easier to read and maintain.

Sample Ex-


pipeline {
  agent any ---------->>run the pipeline on any available agent (node) in the Jenkins environment.
    stages {
         stage ('build') {
           steps {
             echo 'this is build stage'
             }
           }
         stage ('build') {
           steps {
             echo 'this is build stage'
             }
           }
         stage ('build') {
           steps {
             echo 'this is build stage'
             }
           }
